From {{etyl|es|en}} {{term|tomate|lang=es}}, from {{etyl|nci|en}} {{term|tomatl|lang=nci}}, {{term|xitomatl|xītomatl|lang=nah}}. <!-- Is "(xi)" part of the Nahuatl word or does this syntax represent "'xitomatl' or 'tomatl'"? Either way, the Nahuatl word should be linked. ANSWER: Xitomatl is the large variety that we are more familiar with, and tomatl is the small tomatillo. However, some dialects of Nahuatl call even the large tomatoes tomatl. The basic form of the word is tomatl, and the prefix xi- is an augmentative. -->

